The '''Okorokov effect''' ({{Lang-ru|эффект Окорокова}}) is the name given to ''resonant coherent excitation'' of heavy [[ion]]s moving in crystals under channeling conditions. V. Okorokov predicted this effect in 1965 and it was first observed by [[Sheldon Datz]] in 1978.


